# MetaLang Implementation Walkthrough

We have successfully established the MetaLang monorepo foundation and implemented the core engine for cross-linguistic terminology alignment.

## üèóÔ∏è Monorepo Structure

Developed as a `pnpm` monorepo with scoped packages:

- **[@metalang/schema](file:///Users/woutersoudan/Desktop/metalang/packages/schema)**: Core TypeScript interfaces and JSON Schemas defining the ontology.
- **[@metalang/core](file:///Users/woutersoudan/Desktop/metalang/packages/core)**: The central registry and normalization engine.
- **[@metalang/plugin-ud](file:///Users/woutersoudan/Desktop/metalang/packages/plugin-ud)**: Universal Dependencies mapping provider.

## üöÄ Key Features

### 1. Canonical Registry
The [Registry](file:///Users/woutersoudan/Desktop/metalang/packages/core/src/registry.ts#3-67) class handles seed data loading and plugin registration, providing a stable pivot point for all linguistic tags.

```typescript
import { Registry } from '@metalang/core';
const registry = new Registry();
registry.loadSeed(seedData);
registry.registerTagSystem(udPlugin);
```

### 2. Tag Normalization
External tags (like `ADJ` from UD) are successfully mapped to canonical MetaLang GUIDs with full multilingual support.

### 3. Hierarchical Graph support
Supports walking the ontology DAG (Direct Acyclic Graph) to resolve parent-child relationships between concepts.

